ionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes FitzSimon was born about 1150, in England, United Kingdom, her father, Simon FitzSimon, was 27 and her mother, Isabel de Cuckney, was 32. She had at least 1 son with Walter de Fauconberge."},"et":{"Abt 1150–":"umbes 1150–Surnud","1150–1190":"1150–1190","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1160–1242":"1160–1242","1140–1216":"1140–1216","1189–1230":"1189–1230","1125–1167":"1125–1167","1120–1167":"1120–1167","1190":"1190","1242":"1242","1120":"1120","1230":"1230","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1216":"1216","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1125":"1125","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","about 1189":"umbes 1189","Withernwick, Yorkshire, England":"Withernwick, Yorkshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1150–":"noin 1150–Kuollut","1150–1190":"1150–1190","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1160–1242":"1160–1242","1140–1216":"1140–1216","1189–1230":"1189–1230","1125–1167":"1125–1167","1120–1167":"1120–1167","1190":"1190","1242":"1242","1120":"1120","1230":"1230","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1216":"1216","Abt 1150":"noin 1150","1125":"1125","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","about 1189":"noin 1189","Withernwick, Yorkshire, Englan